VarAttributes.CATDESC: [FLUX] Proton number flux, 15 energy channels populated approximately 0.4-3 keV [spectrogram]
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Proton number flux in 14 energy channels populated from about 0.6 keV to about 10 keV.  Channel energies vary with time, keeping the peak flux in channel 10.  Channel 15 is the lowest energy channel.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> Time-variable energy in each of 15 channels
---> Time-variable energy in each of 15 channels
Mom.P.TIME. Unix time, seconds since January 1, 1970
[DO NOT USE / NOT POPULATED?] [P.SC_POT] Spacecraft potential estimated from proton ONLY measurements
[P.SC_CURRENT?] Current contribution to the spacecraft from thermal protons
---> [P.MAGF] magnetic field vector interpolated (linearly) to the time of the PESA Low distribution, in GSE cartesian components
---> [P.FLUX] Proton total number flux - cartesian GSE
[P.PTENS] Proton Pressure Tensor calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to, in the following order: XX, YY, ZZ, XY, XZ, YZ
---> [P.MFTENS] Proton Momentum Flux Tensor calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to, in the following order: XX, YY, ZZ, XY, XZ, YZ
---> [P.T3] Proton Temperature eigenvalues after diagonalization of tensor, calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to:  XX, YY, ZZ
[P.SYMM] Symmetry direction of proton pressure tensor, calculated in the GSE coordinate basis.  The elements correspond to:  XX, YY, ZZ and are defined by the largest eigenvalue in .T3
---> [P.SYMM_ANG] Angle between proton symmetry direction and the magnetic field vector
VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: Angle of proton symmetry direction to B

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> [P.SYMM_MAGT3] Proton temperature tensor... rotated into a field-aligned coordinate basis and then taking the diagonal elements only
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The elements then correspond to:  Perp_1, Perp_2, Parallel (with respect to .MAGF). Let V = .VELOCITY, B = .MAGF, then: Perp_1 = (B x V) x B, Perp_2 = (B x V) and Then T_perp = (MAGT3[0] + MAGT3[1])/2.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: [P.ERANGE] Proton energy range used to compute the moments
